Sentencas: The effect of Sr doping in CeO2 for its use as solid electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) has been explored here.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Ce1-xSrxO2-delta (x = 0.05-0.2) are successfully synthesized by citrate-complexation method.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: XRD, Raman, FT-IR, FE-SEM/EDX and electrochemical impedance spectra are used for structural and electrical characterizations.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The formation of well crystalline cubic fluorite structured solid solution is observed for x = 0.05 based on XRD and Raman spectra.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: For compositions i.e., x > 0.05, however, a secondary phase of SrCeO3 is confirmed by the peak at 342 cm(-1) in Raman spectra.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Although the oxygen ion conductivity was found to decrease with increase in x, based on ac-impedance studies, conductivity of Ce0.95Sr0.05O2-delta was found to be higher than of Ce0.95Gd0.1O2-delta and Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The decrease in conductivity of Ce1-xSrxO2-delta with increasing dopant concentration is ascribed to formation of impurity phase SrCeO3 as well as the formation of neutral associated pairs, Se '' Ce V-o.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The activation energies are found to be 0.77, 0.83, 0.85 and 0.90 eV for x = 0.05, 0.1, 0.15 and 0.20, respectively.
Titulo: Investigation on the Sr-doped ceria Ce1-xSrO2-δ (x=0.05-0.2) as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature SOFC
